example.statement:
					For each of the following functions, use the appropriate formulas to find the derivative.  Then, find an equation for the tangent line to the function at the given point.


 S(p) = \sqrt{p}-p at (9,-6)



 F(r) = \dfrac{5}{r^3} at (-2,-5/8)



 A(r) = \pi r^2 at (1,\pi)



 F(y) = \lrpar{\dfrac{1}{y^2}-\dfrac{3}{y^4}}(y+5y^3) at (-1,12)



 J(v) = (v^3-2v)(v^{-4}+v^{-2}) at (1,-4)



 f(x) = \dfrac{1+2x}{3-4x} at \lrpar{\dfrac{1}{2},1}



 Y(t)=\dfrac{1}{t^3+2t^2-1} at \lrpar{\dfrac{1}{2},-\dfrac{8}{3}}



 h(u) = \dfrac{(u+2)^2}{1-u} at (2,-16)



 f(t) = \dfrac{\sqrt[3]{t}}{t-3} at \lrpar{8,\dfrac{2}{5}}

Suppose that f(4) = 2, g(4) = 5, f'(4) = 6, and g'(4) = -3.  Find h'(4) if:



		h(x) = 3f(x) + 8g(x)




		h(x) = f(x)g(x)




		h(x) = \dfrac{f(x)}{g(x)}




		h(x) = \dfrac{g(x)}{f(x) + g(x)}

If f is a differentiable function, find an expression for the derivative of each of the following:



		y = x^3f(x)




		y = \dfrac{f(x)}{x}




		y = \dfrac{x^2}{f(x)}




		y = \dfrac{1 + xf(x)}{\sqrt{x}}
